BNP PARIBAS OPEN
March 9, 2019
Alexander Zverev
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
A. ZVEREV/M. Klizan   
6-3, 2-0 [Ret.]   
THE MODERATOR: Questions, please.   
 Q.  Tennis is a sport largely about crafting a career based on the decisions you make.  Again, you don't have to answer this question if you're not feeling well, but my question is:  What do you feel is the best decision that you made in your career that has helped you?  
ALEXANDER ZVEREV: I don't think there is one.  I think there is always multiple.  I think you always have to make the right choice to be at the top.  You can never make bad decisions.  You can never make -- you know, decisions that sometimes you want to, but you have to be professional and you have to, you know, first of all enjoy it, but at the same time focus on your goal, focus on your dream and let everything else be secondary.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT